OL,3,CCouncillor faced official complaint
OL,4,Cfor refusing to sign card
OL,6,FCouncillors blamed increased media
OL,7,Fcoverage of meetings and a "changing
OL,8,Fculture" for the rise in complaints.
OL,10,FOf the 28 complaints that were
OL,11,Freferred for investigation just one
OL,12,Fhas been completed. This judged the
OL,13,Fcouncillor had not breached the
OL,14,Fcouncil's code of conduct.
OL,16,FThe committee acknowledged that more
OL,17,Fresources are needed to match the
OL,18,Fnumber of complaints.
