OL,3,CCouncillor faced official complaint
OL,4,Cfor refusing to sign card
OL,6,FAn officer told the meeting: "The
OL,7,Ffigures were higher than previously
OL,8,Fand at an exceptional level. The time
OL,9,Ftaken to assess and handle all the
OL,10,Fcomplaints was substantial."
OL,12,FThe meeting also heard that a cross-
OL,13,Fparty group had been set up to look at
OL,14,Fbeefing up security for councillors
OL,15,Fafter concerns were raised about the
OL,16,Fpublic being a potential threat at
OL,17,Fopen meetings.
OL,19,FHowever, they noted the issue was
OL,20,Fbeing caused by a small minority of
OL,21,Fpeople.
